Transpiling 

- Transpile is a portmanteau of the words translate and compile. 
- Compilers typically compile a written programming language into a incomprehensible machine code.
- A transpiler is a special kind of compiler that translates from the source code of one programming language 
  to the source code of another. 

  Steps to set up a transpiler: babel

  mkdir project name 
  cd project_name
  npm init -y

  npm install babel-cli --save-dev
  npm install babel-preset-es2015 --save-dev

  test:
  nvim index.js
    let foo = "bar"; 

  save and run it 

  babel src -d dist // creates a directory called dist for transpiled code

  Interesting plugins: 
  npm install babel-preset-stage-0
  npm install babel-plugin-transform-decorators-legacy
  npm run babel 


